    <field name="abstract_teim">Letters written by United States Army soldier Harry R. Mattson (1894-1956) to his parents in Brooklyn, during World War I, when, as a member of the 106th Regiment, 27th Division, he served in Europe during the Ypres-Lys Offensive and the Somme Offensive.</field>
